{
  "doc_id": "10386",
  "text": "There is growing interest about metabolic dysfunction and/or exercise impact the peripheral and central nervous system, particularly as it relates to neural disease [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . It remains unclear how the genetic differences underlying intrinsic aerobic capacity between LCR and HCR rats alter the peripheral nervous system. Previous studies have reported that LCR rats have increased fat mass and proinflammatory signaling in adipose tissue, as well as alterations in cholinergic anti-inflammatory signaling [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Both are known to be important in peripheral nerve function and pain.",
